  "style": "IEEE",
  "texts": [
    "Performance Modeling: From Profiling to PredictionModeling GPU performance remains challenging due to micro-architectural complexity.",
    "Existing approaches include hybrid analytical + ML models [27][28] which combine static features with dynamic profiling but require extensive data, cycle-accurate simulators [29] which are precise but slow and architecture-specific, application-specific models for FMM [12][13] that rely on hardware coefficients.",
    "Crucially, prior research in GPU performance modeling has consistently identified data locality and cache misses as dominant factors in kernel performance.",
    "Studies such as [35][36][37] [41] have quantitatively demonstrated that poor spatial locality leads to high cache miss rates, which in turn impose severe penalties due to long memory latencies on GPUs.",
    "The spatial locality is the same important in many-core architectures [38]."
  ],
